parameters: Oh, did you find the antenna?
Yes, I found it when I went to the waterfall.
Good, good. Kenta will fix it for us.
As expected, Kenta senpai! You're so versatile!
What are you all talking about so happily?

Today, I tried making fish cutlets. There's still a lot of
oil left, so...
Well, I don't know how much we should be saving, but...

You don't think we can't leave until we use all of it,
right? Hahaha!

Hey, boss! What would you do if the words you're saying
became reality?
Ah, yeah. I found an antenna.
I can contact the outside now.

Oh my... Doing it outside... That's truly perverted...
No, I mean, precious...
Ahahaha! You have such a stupid face! It's hilarious!
Pfft, now, water. Calm down a bit.

Thank you so much. I'm sorry for disturbing you with my
voice...

Interesting things happen one by one every day, don't they? How
about trying to debut? Aim for being the best in Japan!
Well, how about a personal broadcast or something?
There's a question mark attached to your words.
Uwaa, I can't even do a Google search here.
Tsugumi-chan! This fish cutlet is really delicious!
Hehe, thank you very much, Kanae. Please enjoy it.
Alright~ I have to eat a lot!
Oh, if you eat a lot, I think you'll gain weight.
...Then, I'll have to eat a little more.
What does a little more mean?

Because I'm looking for an antenna, I feel like my island life
is coming to an end. The already lively dinner time
became even more noisy.

While happily watching the club members making a lively
commotion, I took a bite of the fish cutlet.

Tsugumi looked at me with a pitiful expression on their face
as a bonus.

Is this the thrilling feeling that Saruyama is talking
about...
